properties.more information: This environmental sculpture is based on endangered species and the restoration of indigenous habitat. The project spans approximately l/3 of a mile alongside Harney Way en-route to Candlestick Park and includes a butterfly meadow, garter-snake promenade, and shoreline ribbon worm sculpture. The artist’s objective was to transform a major sewage pumping and transport station into an environmental artwork that enhances habitat for a variety of endangered species indigenous to the site.
